# GA Assignment Algorithm: Performance Optimization Plan

## Background

The assignment algorithm is a Genetic Algorithm (GA) in [GeneticEngine.java](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java) that evolves a population of gate-assignment schedules over multiple generations. Profiling the code reveals **5 concrete bottlenecks** that collectively waste a large fraction of CPU time.

---

## Bottleneck Analysis

### BN-1 — Redundant Fitness Evaluations During Sort (GeneticEngine.java L85-87)

```java
// CURRENT – O(P log P) sorts but calls calculateFitness twice per comparison
population.sort((c1, c2) -> Double.compare(
    evaluator.calculateFitness(c2, flights),
    evaluator.calculateFitness(c1, flights)));
```

A sort on P=200 chromosomes calls [calculateFitness](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/FitnessEvaluator.java#109-247) O(P log P) ≈ **1,530 times per generation** just for ordering. [calculateFitness](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/FitnessEvaluator.java#109-247) itself is an O(N) walk over all flights plus BFS calls. **Fix:** pre-compute fitness for all chromosomes into a `double[]` array once per generation, then sort by index.

---

### BN-2 — Redundant [getBestSolution](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#243-256) scan (GeneticEngine.java L286-287)

After [evolve()](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#79-102) the loop calls [getBestSolution()](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#243-256) which iterates the whole population *again* calling [calculateFitness](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/FitnessEvaluator.java#109-247) P times. Since the sort in [evolve()](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#79-102) already leaves the best chromosome at index 0, [getBestSolution](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#243-256) just needs to return `population.get(0)` — no fitness calls needed.

---

### BN-3 — `new Random()` Per Function Call (GeneticEngine.java L104, L122, L169)

[select()](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#103-118), [crossover()](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#119-139), and [mutate()](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#162-192) each construct `new Random()` on every call. Creating a `Random` is not entirely free, and more importantly, each new instance is seeded from `System.nanoTime()` — with rapid sequential calls they can share seeds, degrading randomness and wasting allocations. **Fix:** make `rand` a single private field on [GeneticEngine](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#16-381).

---

### BN-4 — [getValidGates](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#140-161) Iterates All Gates on Every Mutation (GeneticEngine.java L140-160)

[getValidGates(f, evaluator)](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#140-161) does two full linear scans of `gates` for every mutation call. With P mutations per generation and G gates this is O(P×G) per generation just for mutation. **Fix:** pre-build a `Map<PlaneType, Map<Boolean, List<Gate>>>` lookup table when the engine starts, so [getValidGates](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#140-161) becomes an O(1) map lookup.

---

### BN-5 — [getConflictIndices](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#193-242) Rebuilds `gateMap` On Every Conflict-Check (GeneticEngine.java L199-201)

```java
Map<Integer, Gate> gateMap = new HashMap<>();
for (Gate g : gates) gateMap.put(g.getId(), g);
```
This rebuilds the same identical map inside every call to [getConflictIndices()](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#193-242). **Fix:** promote `gateMap` to a private field initialized once in the constructor (it already exists in [FitnessEvaluator](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/FitnessEvaluator.java#25-248); [GeneticEngine](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#16-381) should maintain its own).

---

## Proposed Changes

### GeneticEngine.java

#### [MODIFY] [GeneticEngine.java](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java)
- Add a single `private final Random rand` field (fixes BN-3).
- Add a `private Map<Integer, Gate> gateMap` field built in the constructor (fixes BN-5).
- Add a `private Map<PlaneType, Map<Boolean, List<Gate>>> validGatesCache` built in the constructor for instant valid-gate lookups (fixes BN-4).
- Refactor [evolve()](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#79-102): pre-compute `double[] fitnessCache` once per generation, sort by pre-computed values, pass the cache to [getBestSolution](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#243-256) (fixes BN-1).
- Refactor [getBestSolution()](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#243-256): since population is already sorted after [evolve()](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#79-102), just return `population.get(0)` — or accept the cache array (fixes BN-2).
- Update [select()](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#103-118), [crossover()](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#119-139), [mutate()](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#162-192), [getConflictIndices()](file:///c:/YudGimel/AIRPORT-version1.0/src/model/algo/genetic/GeneticEngine.java#193-242) to use the shared field-level objects.

